ashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [24, 28], "text": "SPY"}, {"indices": [33, 37], "text": "QQQ"}, {"indices": [71, 77], "text": "GOOGL"}, {"indices": [79, 83], "text": "CAT"}, {"indices": [85, 89], "text": "LLY"}, {"indices": [95, 100], "text": "AAPL"}], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": null, "retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}}, {"reason": "cashtags=5", "tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050564793736503359", "url": "https://x.com/ResearchPulse1/status/2050564793736503359", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/ResearchPulse1/status/2050564793736503359", "text": "Trump yesterday started to push MFN deal with $LLY $NVO. \n\nThe deal where LLY and NVO lower their price to $245 for Tirzepatide (Mounjaro and Zepbound) plus semaglutide (Ozempic pen, Ozempic pill, wegovy pen and wegovy pill) \n\nWhere the senior only have to pay $50 to get acces to obesity meds. \n\nIn a time where he\u2019s never been more unpopular, this deal is one of the very positive and popular stories he can use to divert attention from Iran etc. \n\nUp until now I have said I want too see the Medicare deal go live. That I could see the administration put a cap on how many seniors will be allowed to acces these much lower prices. \n\nFor each million seniors at Medicare, the cost for the government will be  about $2.3B upfront. \n\nHowever since the price will also apply all those who already are using these meds in Medicare = savings for the government. \n\nThis means the first 2-3 million extra seniors will be cost neutral for MediCare. \n\nIf 10 million gets acces it will cost +$15B upfront for Medicare. \n\nHow much is Trump willing to spend\u2026\u2026.\n\nThe more he promotes the deal as he did yesterday, the more likely he will accept a higher cost and thereby more seniors to get acces. \n\nFor both $LLY and $NVO this is very high on their agenda. How to convert as many seniors as possible \n\n$VKTX", "